Political contestants and voters in Nyandarua should make peace a priority, Cecilia Mbuthia, Nyandarua JP governor nominee Francis Kimemia&rsquo;s running mate, has said.&ldquo;Peace is very important, not only for the aspirants, but also for the voters. We should preach peace wherever we go,&rdquo; she saidMbuthia spoke on Wednesday afternoon at Ol Kalou Catholic Hall during a peace forum convened by Nyandarua county commissioner Samuel Kimiti.She urged politicians to campaign on issues and stop insulting one another and engaging in activities that may cause trouble &ldquo;so that we get through the elections without people being injured&rdquo;.Mbuthia cautioned politicians against disrupting rivals&rsquo; meetings.